## TigerBeetle's Convention: `assert` for Programming Errors

TigerBeetle's convention is **unambiguous and consistent**: invalid arguments representing programming errors are validated with `assert(std.debug.assert)`, not with `error` returns, `@panic`, or `unreachable`. The pattern is pervasive throughout the entire codebase. Here's a precise breakdown.

---

### The Core Rule: `assert` is the tool for programming invariants

`assert` maps directly to Zig's `std.debug.assert`, which panics in Debug/ReleaseSafe and is **undefined behavior (removed) in ReleaseFast/ReleaseSmall**. This is intentional — TigerBeetle treats violated invariants as bugs, not recoverable conditions.

The canonical import at the top of every file:

```zig
// src/lsm/schema.zig, src/stdx/prng.zig, src/vsr/clock.zig, ...
const assert = std.debug.assert;
```

---

### Pattern 1: `assert` at the top of `init` to validate parameters

This is the **dominant pattern** for factory/init functions. Every parameter constraint is stated as an `assert` before any computation.

**[`src/lsm/schema.zig` — `TableIndex.init`](https://github.com/tigerbeetle/tigerbeetle/blob/main/src/lsm/schema.zig#L120-L158):**

```zig
const Parameters = struct {
    key_size: u32,
    value_block_count_max: u32,
};

pub fn init(parameters: Parameters) TableIndex {
    assert(parameters.key_size > 0);
    assert(parameters.value_block_count_max > 0);
    assert(parameters.value_block_count_max <= constants.lsm_table_value_blocks_max);

    // ... compute derived fields ...
    return .{ ... };
}
```

**[`src/lsm/scan_merge.zig` — `ScanMerge.init`](https://github.com/tigerbeetle/tigerbeetle/blob/main/src/lsm/scan_merge.zig#L153-L167):**

```zig
pub fn init(scans: []const *Scan) ScanMerge {
    assert(scans.len > 0);
    assert(scans.len <= constants.lsm_scans_max);

    const direction_first = scans[0].direction();
    const snapshot_first = scans[0].snapshot();

    if (scans.len > 1) for (scans[1..]) |scan| {
        assert(scan.direction() == direction_first);
        assert(scan.snapshot() == snapshot_first);
    };
    // ...
}
```

**[`src/vsr/clock.zig` — `Clock.init`](https://github.com/tigerbeetle/tigerbeetle/blob/main/src/vsr/clock.zig#L200-L205):**

```zig
