    assert(options.quorum > 0);
    assert(options.quorum <= options.replica_count);
    if (options.replica_count > 1) assert(options.quorum > 1);
    // ...
}
```

Note: `Clock.init` returns `!Clock` (can error) because it allocates memory — but the parameter validation still uses `assert`, not errors.

**[`src/stdx/prng.zig` — `PRNG.ratio` and `ZipfianGenerator.init_theta`](https://github.com/tigerbeetle/tigerbeetle/blob/main/src/stdx/prng.zig#L104-L107):**

