### Applied to your `Span.init(base: u8)`

Following TigerBeetle's convention exactly:

```zig
pub fn init(base: u8) Span {
    assert(std.ascii.isAlphabetic(base));
    return .{ .base = base };
}
```

One `assert` per invariant, no error union, no `@panic`. The function signature stays clean (`Span`, not `!Span`), and the assertion documents and enforces the contract. If `base` could be checked at comptime, wrap it: `comptime assert(std.ascii.isAlphabetic(base))`.
